◆ equilDiffFluxFacsP()

void equilDiffFluxFacsP ( double *const  p_F)

Computes the vector of elemental mass and energy diffusion fluxes per pressure gradient for a mixture in equilibrium, \(\mathcal{F}_k^p\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^p\), where.

\[ \mathcal{F}_k^p = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i \frac{M_{w,k}}{M_{w,i}} \nu_i^k \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \left( \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial p} + \frac{x_j - y_j}{p} \right), \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}, \]

and

\[ \mathcal{F}_h^p = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \left( \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial p} + \frac{x_j - y_j}{p} \right). \]

The total mass diffusion flux of element \(k\) for a mixture at equilibrium can then be computed with

\[ \rho_k V_k = \mathcal{F}_k^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_k^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_k^{z_l} \nabla z_l, \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}. \]

The total energy diffusion flux is computed by

\[ \sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i V_i = \mathcal{F}_h^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_h^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_h^{z_l} \nabla z_l. \]

Parameters
p_F- A vector with length greater than the number of elements plus one. On return, the vector will correspond to \(\{\mathcal{F}^p_1, \cdots, \mathcal{F}^p_{N_e}, \mathcal{F}^p_h\}\).
See also
equilDiffFluxFacsT for \(\mathcal{F}_k^T\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^T\)
equilDiffFluxFacsZ for \(\mathcal{F}_k^{z_l}\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^{z_l}\)

Definition at line 413 of file Transport.cpp.

◆ equilDiffFluxFacsT()

void equilDiffFluxFacsT ( double *const  p_F)

Computes the vector of elemental mass and energy diffusion fluxes per temperature gradient for a mixture in equilibrium, \(\mathcal{F}_k^T\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^T\), where.

\[ \mathcal{F}_k^T = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i \frac{M_{w,k}}{M_{w,i}} \nu_i^k \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \left( \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial T} + \frac{k_{Tj}}{T} \right), \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}, \]

and

\[ \mathcal{F}_h^T = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \left( \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial T} + \frac{k_{Tj}}{T} \right). \]

The total mass diffusion flux of element \(k\) for a mixture at equilibrium can then be computed with

\[ \rho_k V_k = \mathcal{F}_k^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_k^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_k^{z_l} \nabla z_l, \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}. \]

The total energy diffusion flux is computed by

\[ \sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i V_i = \mathcal{F}_h^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_h^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_h^{z_l} \nabla z_l. \]

Parameters
p_F- A vector with length greater than the number of elements plus one. On return, the vector will correspond to \(\{\mathcal{F}^T_1, \cdots, \mathcal{F}^T_{N_e}, \mathcal{F}^T_h\}\).
See also
equilDiffFluxFacsP for \(\mathcal{F}_k^p\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^p\)
equilDiffFluxFacsZ for \(\mathcal{F}_k^{z_l}\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^{z_l}\)

Definition at line 433 of file Transport.cpp.

◆ equilDiffFluxFacsZ()

void equilDiffFluxFacsZ ( double *const  p_F)

Computes the matrix of elemental mass and energy diffusion fluxes per elemental mole fraction gradients for a mixture in equilibrium, \(\mathcal{F}_k^{z_l}\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^{z_l}\), where.

\[ \mathcal{F}_k^{z_l} = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i \frac{M_{w,k}}{M_{w,i}} \nu_i^k \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial z_l}, \quad \forall\;k,l\in\mathcal{E}, \]

and

\[ \mathcal{F}_h^{z_l} = -\sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i \sum_{j\in\mathcal{S}} D_{ij} \frac{\partial x_j}{\partial z_l}, \quad \forall\;l\in\mathcal{E}. \]

The total mass diffusion flux of element \(k\) for a mixture at equilibrium can then be computed with

\[ \rho_k V_k = \mathcal{F}_k^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_k^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_k^{z_l} \nabla z_l, \quad \forall\;k\in\mathcal{E}. \]

The total energy diffusion flux is computed by

\[ \sum_{i\in\mathcal{S}} \rho_i h_i V_i = \mathcal{F}_h^p \nabla p + \mathcal{F}_h^T \nabla T + \sum_{l\in\mathcal{E}} \mathcal{F}_h^{z_l} \nabla z_l. \]

Parameters
p_F- A pointer to a ( \(N_e+1\times N_e\)) matrix stored in row-major order. On return, the matrix will correspond to

\[ \begin{bmatrix} \mathcal{F}_1^{z_1} & \cdots & \mathcal{F}_1^{z_{N_e}} \\ \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\ \mathcal{F}_{N_e}^{z_1} & \cdots & \mathcal{F}_{N_e}^{z_{N_e}} \\ \mathcal{F}_h^{z_1} & \cdots & \mathcal{F}_h^{z_{N_e}} \end{bmatrix}. \]

See also
equilDiffFluxFacsP for \(\mathcal{F}_k^p\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^p\)
equilDiffFluxFacsT for \(\mathcal{F}_k^T\) and \(\mathcal{F}_h^T\)

◆ stefanMaxwell() [1/2]

void stefanMaxwell ( const double *const  p_dp,
double *const  p_V,
double &  E,
int  order = 1 
)

Computes the species diffusion velocities and ambipolar electric field using the Ramshaw approximation of the generalized Stefan-Maxwell equations and the supplied modified driving forces.

\[ d^{'}_i = \frac{\nabla p_i}{n k_B T_h} - \frac{y_i p}{n k_B T_h} \nabla \ln p + k^h_{Ti} \nabla \ln T_h + k^e_{Ti} \frac{T_h}{T_e} \nabla \ln T_e \]

Todo:
Check that this is correct for thermal nonequilibrium.
Parameters
p_dp- the vector of modified driving forces \( d^{'}_i \)
p_V- on return, the vector of diffusion velocities
E- on return, the ambipolar electric field

◆ stefanMaxwell() [2/2]

void stefanMaxwell ( double  Th,
double  Te,
const double *const  p_dp,
double *const  p_V,
double &  E,
int  order = 1 
)

Computes the species diffusion velocities and ambipolar electric field using the Ramshaw approximation of the generalized Stefan-Maxwell equations and the supplied modified driving forces.

\[ d^{'}_i = \frac{\nabla p_i}{n k_B T_h} - \frac{y_i p}{n k_B T_h} \nabla \ln p + k^h_{Ti} \nabla \ln T_h + k^e_{Ti} \frac{T_h}{T_e} \nabla \ln T_e \]

Parameters
Th- heavy particle translational temperature
Te- free electron translational temperature
p_dp- the vector of modified driving forces \( d^{'}_i \)
p_V- on return, the vector of diffusion velocities
E- on return, the ambipolar electric field
